The paper deals with algorithms for classical graph problems such as bridges, topological sorting, and strongly connected components. These problems are typically studied in the context of data structures (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), computational geometry (cs.CG), and graph theory (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses space-efficient algorithms, which could also fall under the category of information theory (cs.IT).
